    "body": "If necessary, yes, kernels can create those files at install time - JSON is easy to create. But it won't always be necessary. With Python, you can use `python -m module` which is independent of the location of the module. With R, you can do `R -e \"module::func()\"`, which also doesn't depend on the install location.\n"
