    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "hi again,\n\nI whish you would for 3.0.1 , cut the line in two steps, so I can easily implement my `personnal` hack, without having it broken  later when you will decide (or not) on a change:\n\ncurrent\n\n```\n        with io.open(kernel_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            kernel_dict = json.load(f)\n```\n\nwish of two  separated lines:\n\n```\n        with io.open(kernel_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            kernel_string = '\\n'.join(f.readlines())\n            kernel_dict = json.loads(kernel_string)\n```\n\nGiven the size of the kernel.json, it won't kill performance.\nThat way, I could implement a hack on kernel_string, without it being destroyed in 3.1\n\nOf course if you decide before 3.0.1 that you will do nothing , the demand is pointless\n"
  },
